videoDescription: A Full Stack application using React, Node.js, Express, MySQL for the front-end and back-end. A web app created for dental professionals and dental offices to find each other.

Front-end lead of a team of 4. A 24 hour hackathon sponsored by Telus with the aim of tackling the theme: Consumers are experiencing option paralysis. The solution: a feature with Artificial Intelligence that provides a list of shows that you may like based on an entry and where you can find them.
An Inventory Management website that was built in collaboration with three of my peers using all we learned and adding MySQL, Knex.js, Jira and Gitflow best practices.
Lead of the front-end. Given 8 hours and a team of 3, were taked with building a full-stack application using React, Node.js and Express.js for the front-end and the back-end
Using React and Axios for the front-end nd Node.js with Express.js for the back-end I was able to build a full-stack application similar to YouTube.
Joining a team of 2, we were tasked with building a functioning application in 4 hours using HTML, CSS/Sass, JS for the front-end, and Axios to pull data from an external API.
A project with JS and axios to build a more interactive and dynamic page.
Using HTML, CSS/Sass + BEM naming conventions, I created a coffee shop landing and menu page.
